# 4. 完璧なトレーニングメニュー

Tsukasa: Wait, Kiritani... You expect us to do all of these things?!
Tsukasa: You have everything scheduled down to the minute. Not only that, it says to do “at least” a hundred reps for each of these drills and exercises!
Akito: Also, what's written for me looks different from what she's written for you.
Tsukasa: What?!
Akito: I'm supposed to run five kilometers and do three sets of a hundred squats and twenty-second planks... And that's before heading to school.
Tsukasa: You're right. That's different from what I have here. I'm supposed to run, do push-ups and one-legged balancing exercises.
Tsukasa: After school, I'm supposed to run home, then run another eight kilometers. Following that, I have to do single-leg bridges and fingertip push-ups...
Tsukasa: And there's more. Strength exercises, straddle splits, more push-ups, back stretches... More one-legged stands, more planking, airplanes, leg cradles...
Tsukasa: Finally, how much time we should be spending each day exercising and sleeping, as well as when to go to bed and wake up...
Akito: So this is why you asked us for “very detailed” schedules on how we spend each day...
Haruka: I tried to come up with drills and exercises that you both could do whenever you had a minute, since I know that you're both very busy with rehearsals and singing practice.
Haruka: Oh, I almost forgot to give you these weights. Please put them on whenever you exercise, to maximize your gains.
Akito: Weights?!
Haruka: I also came up with diets for each of you to follow until the day of the event. I wrote down the recipes for everything that you'll be having, along with why I chose them.
Tsukasa: You went that far?!
Haruka: Yes. Since we'll be training together, I wanted to come up with the most effective solutions for us.
Tsukasa: Yes, it will be important for us to eat right in order to get in shape... But you have our protein and fat intakes down to the gram.
Akito: Like what athletes do...
Haruka: This is the least we need to do in order to win.
Tsukasa: Hmm... Yes, you have a point. Just finishing my stage is going to require a tremendous amount of strength and stamina.
Tsukasa: This is going to be very hard, but I should be able to manage. I endured everything Mikazukigumi threw at me, after all.
Tsukasa: So, challenge accepted!
Akito: Yeah, this is really well put together. We should be a lot stronger once we get through it...
Tsukasa: Yes, but still... You came up with these all by yourself, Kiritani?
Haruka: Oh... I actually had a little help from a friend...
Haruka: Here. This is the Shinobi Battle website.
MEIKO: Crossing a log bridge, becoming a water spider, jumping between hanging poles... This looks like a wonderfully fun obstacle course!
MEIKO: Thinking of ways to train for this should be quite a lot of fun.
Haruka: Hehe. I know what you mean. We'll be doing most of these for the first time, so devising strategies for them is really enjoyable.
Haruka: But we're in this to win, and I wasn't sure I'd be able to handle it all by myself. So, MEIKO, I really appreciate you helping me like this.
MEIKO: No need to thank me! I said that I wanted to do this, didn't I♪
Haruka: Thank you. Still, you really do enjoy coming up with workouts and such, don't you?
MEIKO: Yes, I do!
MEIKO: Working towards a goal, trying to figure out what you're missing, thinking about what you need to do, clearing checkpoints as you go along...
MEIKO: Knowing that you're making progress towards your dream little by little is a wonderful feeling, no?
Haruka: *Nod* I know what you mean.
Haruka: And once you've accomplished everything, you start thinking about what to pursue next.
MEIKO: Hehe. I knew you'd say that, Haruka.
MEIKO: So, let's start brainstorming, shall we?!
MEIKO: Starting with the log bridge. Your teammate's core and abs need to be very strong for this, so...
MEIKO: I know! Wouldn't doing L-sit pull-ups be the best option?
Haruka: Yes, that would be... But I feel like I'd be asking too much of him.
Haruka: Instead, what if we had him do one-arm handstands? His goal would be to remain perfectly still.
MEIKO: Yes... No, that's also asking quite a lot of him!
Haruka: Oh, you think so? Then...
Haruka: I wouldn't have been able to come up with training schedules specifically designed for each of you without her help.
Haruka: However, we all have our strengths and weaknesses, so I'd like to make adjustments as needed as we go along.
Tsukasa: I see... Now that I know how much effort you and your friend put into these, we have to do our best to succeed!
Akito: That's not going to be easy...
Akito: But I made a commitment. So, let's give it everything we have.
Haruka: Yes, let's!
Haruka: So, let's start training right away!
Tsukasa: I'm supposed to start by doing a hundred underhand chin-ups.
Haruka: Yes. The log bridge and spider wall obstacles both test your legs and core, but your arms also need to be strong.
Haruka: From what I saw, Tenma, you've already made quite a few core and leg exercises a part of your normal workout routine. So, you should be okay there.
Haruka: Which is why I'm having you start with a focus on strengthening your arm muscles.
Tsukasa: I see. Yes, this really feels like it's been designed just for me!
Tsukasa: Alright, I'll get started.
Haruka: Okay. Then, turn your palms towards your face and grab hold of the bar.
Tsukasa: Grab the bar! Lift myself up and... Hold!
Haruka: Good. Now repeat what you just did.
Tsukasa: Will do! Hmph! Huff! Hnng!
Haruka: Okay, good. You're doing just fine.
Tsukasa: Hah hah hah! A hundred is going to be a piece of cake!
Haruka: Then, can you try wearing this?
Tsukasa: Hm? This looks like... A vest? No, wait! Why's it so heavy...?!
Haruka: Because there are about ten kilograms of weights inside.
Tsukasa: What?! Ten kilograms?! That seems like a bit much, don't you think?!
Haruka: Even just three or four kilograms would usually increase the difficulty level of this exercise significantly, but I'm making a special exception today.
Haruka: Because you never know what's going to happen during the event.
Tsukasa: True... Then, I'll gladly give this a try!
Tsukasa: Hnnnngone! Aaarghtwo! Huff! Huff...! Th-This vest has made things so much more difficult...!
Tsukasa: But I'm not about to give up! I... I will succeed!
Akito: 98, 99, 100... Phew...
Haruka: Nice work. How were those jumping squats?
Akito: Fine... Still, this is harder than I was expecting. My calves are already starting to feel really heavy...
Haruka: Then, that means this exercise is working like I'd hoped. You're going to need to explode over that vault, after all.
Haruka: Your calves feeling heavy is a sign that your muscles are growing.
Haruka: Actually, you look like you can handle a bit more. How about we add some extra weight?
Akito: Huh? Extra weight?
Haruka: Yes. Next, try doing a hundred more while wearing these weighted wristbands.
Haruka: They will feel a little heavy, but I'm sure you'll do just fine, Shinonome.
Akito: ... You're joking, right?
Haruka: ...98, 99, 100. Phew... Okay, that's one set.
Comments: <You're amazing, Haruka...> <Just the fact that you can do one-arm pushups is incredible.> <I can't even do push-ups using both arms!>
Haruka: It's okay to go slow if you're still trying to get the hang of things.
Haruka: For example, if you're just starting today, I recommend doing three sets of ten. After that, you can gradually begin increasing your reps.
Haruka: But if you feel that isn't enough... Well...
Haruka: You can try placing some weights on your back. I'll try doing that now, so sit back and watch me.
Comments: <W-Weights?!> <How can you still move...?> <Well, you are aiming to compete in SHINOBI...>
Comments: <Lemme give that a try.> <Start by doing ten? I think I can do that.> <Will I become more like you if I really keep at it, Haruka?>
Haruka: Okay, I think we've gotten everything we can out of these simulated runs.
Haruka: Why don't we call it a day here?
Tsukasa: Hm? Already? I can still keep going...
Haruka: No, we should stop. Tomorrow's our big day.
Akito: Right. We probably should rest up for tomorrow.
Haruka: Exactly. We don't want any fatigue to linger, so let's do some light stretches and end things here.
Tsukasa: Alright, sounds good!
Tsukasa: Still... It's hard to believe how much muscle we've been able to put on in such a short period.
Akito: I'm also surprised. I feel like we're going to post a really good time.
Tsukasa: Me too. We have you to thank for being such an incredible instructor, Kiritani.
Tsukasa: We were able to become this strong because you showed neither us nor yourself any mercy.
Akito: To be fair, my jaw dropped when I first saw your notebooks...
Akito: But thank you for putting in all that effort, and giving us the best shot possible at winning.
Haruka: Shinonome, Tenma...
Haruka: Hehe. You're both very welcome. Now I'm really glad we decided to form a team.
Haruka: That being said, don't forget that this was all in pursuit of a goal.
Haruka: So, let's make sure we post a good result tomorrow!
Tsukasa & Akito: Let's!
